OL,3,CPolls close in Makerfield by-election
OL,5,FIf he returns to Westminster as an MP,
OL,6,FBurnham is widely expected to
OL,7,Fchallenge Starmer for leadership and
OL,8,Fcould trigger a contest as early as
OL,9,FFriday.
OL,11,FThe Prime Minister has repeatedly made
OL,12,Fclear he has no intention of standing
OL,13,Faside and insists he will fight any
OL,14,Fchallenge to his leadership.
OL,16,FBurnham's closest competitor is Reform
OL,17,FUK's Robert Kenyon. Polls have
OL,18,Fsuggested the party is losing voters
OL,19,Fto Restore Britain, a party with a
OL,20,Fmore hard-line approach to migration
OL,21,Fand other issues.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
